                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13466609" author="jwcarman" created="Mon, 1 Oct 2012 01:39:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I believe this is reported against the wrong component.  The issue actually lies within the HTTP component in the DefaultHttpBinding class.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13466612" author="jwcarman" created="Mon, 1 Oct 2012 01:55:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a patch that implements what I think you&apos;re looking for.  I should probably add a test in the http component also, since that&apos;s where the actual code change takes place.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13466615" author="jwcarman" created="Mon, 1 Oct 2012 02:12:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s another patch that patches both the http and http4 components.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13466616" author="jwcarman" created="Mon, 1 Oct 2012 02:14:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We should really think about consolidating this code.  There are some value-adds in the http component that aren&apos;t in the http4 component.  They&apos;re virtually the same exact code.  There has to be a way to extract a superclass from this and create some abstract supermodule that they can both reference.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13466617" author="njiang" created="Mon, 1 Oct 2012 02:41:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@James,&lt;br/&gt;
Yes, we need to share these code in a common http module to avoid updating the code in camel-http and camel-http4 modules.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13466620" author="njiang" created="Mon, 1 Oct 2012 03:33:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Applied the patch with thanks to James, I also fix the test errors of camel-jetty caused by this change.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13467024" author="jwcarman" created="Mon, 1 Oct 2012 18:06:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry about introducing the test failure.  I saw that late last night and didn&apos;t have time to fix it.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13471370" author="njiang" created="Mon, 8 Oct 2012 02:00:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Applied the patch into trunk, camel-2.10.x and camel-2.9.x branches.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
